						               													<description>Magic Creatures is a card game designed for up to 7 players, age 6 and older.  The deck consists of 70 cards.  20 of these cards are &amp;ldquo;Magic Cards&amp;rdquo;.  The other 50 cards are gameplay cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The magic cards either have a creature and value on one side that gives the card bearer a Skeleton with a &amp;ldquo;Damage Boost&amp;rdquo; point value, or a Ghost with a &amp;ldquo;Health Boost&amp;rdquo; point value. The gameplay cards consist of five distinct &amp;ldquo;suits&amp;rdquo;, with ten cards in each suit.  Each card within each suit displays the suit type, signified by a &amp;ldquo;Magic Creature&amp;rdquo; and a point value for &amp;ldquo;Damage&amp;rdquo;, as well as a point value for &amp;ldquo;Health&amp;rdquo;.  The point values for damage and health vary from one card to the next, even within the same suit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Magic Cards are shuffled and placed face down in a stack on the table.  The gameplay cards are shuffled and dealt to the players.  Each player is dealt one card at a time, face down, for a maximum of ten cards per player.  The youngest player goes first and gameplay continues rotating from one player to the next in a clockwise direction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns using the gameplay cards in their hands and the Magic Cards on the table to &amp;quot;attack&amp;quot; other players. The damage and health values on the cards are used to determine the winner. The loser of an attempted attack loses his/her gameplay card. The last player with gameplay cards remaining in their hand wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
